The paper focuses on content-based multimedia information retrieval, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper specifically deals with repositories of image/text multimedia objects, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses graph-based methods for information fusion, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper includes empirical analysis and provides insights and guidelines, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
